# Escalation Procedures

This document outlines when and how to escalate issues beyond the operator level.

## When to Escalate

### Immediate Escalation (Severity 1)
- Complete system outage
- Security incidents
- Data corruption or loss
- Multiple critical service failures

### Escalate Within 2 Hours (Severity 2)
- Partial system outage affecting multiple users
- Performance degradation impacting business operations
- Failed backup or disaster recovery procedures
- Authentication or authorization failures

### Escalate Within 8 Hours (Severity 3)
- Single service degradation
- Non-critical feature failures
- Capacity planning concerns
- Minor configuration issues

